pr_body:
Hello, 

This pull requests added support for three tiered structures. Also keys in the structures with the same names will be merged. For example:

The template:
```
template {
    key1 = 4 
}
template {
    key2 = 6
}
```
evalulates to:
```
{
    template': {
        'key1': 4,
        'key2': 6
    }
}
```
The template:
```
foo "bar" "baz" {
    key = 4
}
foo "bar" "qux" {
    key = 5
}
foo "bar" "biz" {
    key = 11
}
```
evalulates to:
```
{
    'foo': {
        'bar': {
            'baz': {'key': 4},
            'biz': {'key': 11},
            'qux': {'key': 5}
        }
    }
}
```
The template:
```
bar "foo" "qux" {
    key = 8
}
bar "foo" "biz" {
    key = 9
    key2 = 3
}   
baz "foo" "biz" { 
    key = 9
    key5 = "somestring"
}
```
evalulates to:
```
{
    'bar': {
        'foo': {
            'biz': {
                'key': 9, 
                'key2': 3
            }, 
           'qux': {
               'key': 8
           }
    }
    'baz': {
        'foo': {
            'biz': {
                'key': 9,
                'key5': u'somestring'
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Also the test runner did not work with the current version of pytest for me. Please let me know what you think.

Thanks!
  Derrick

Helpful with custom FunctionJob/Job implementations. 

Currently to support any extra params of custom `job_class` by decorator a copy of `decorators.cacheback` decorator would have to be added. With this diff applied users can specify own `job_class` with any number of `job_class` params. 

@codeinthehole If needed happy to update docs as well

For example, for the common case where the Serializer has per-request custom behavior, users can instruct `DjangoSerializerType` to pass the request through context:
```python
class UserType(DjangoSerializerType):
    
    @classmethod
    def get_serializer_kwargs(cls, root, info, **kwargs):
        return {'context': {'request': info.context}}
    
    class Meta:
        serializer_class = UserSerializer
```

I only implemented this for `DjangoSerializerType` and not `DjangoSerializerMutation`.

Fixes #698 

Not sure of the best place to update documentation to reflect this change.

